### Ridged API - Authentication Endpoints Testing
### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5081
@email = testuser@example.com
@password = SecurePass123!

###
### 1. Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "confirmPassword": "{{password}}",
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "User"
}

###
### 2. Verify Email (Copy token from registration response)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "PASTE_VERIFICATION_TOKEN_HERE"
}

###
### 3. Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

###
### 4. Refresh Token (Use tokens from login response)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/refresh-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accessToken": "PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE",
  "refreshToken": "PASTE_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

###
### 5. Forgot Password
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}"
}

###
### 6. Reset Password (Use token from forgot password response)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "PASTE_RESET_TOKEN_HERE",
  "newPassword": "NewSecurePass123!",
  "confirmPassword": "NewSecurePass123!"
}

